sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Expresses the glgC, glgA, and glgS proteins/enzymes usually not expressed in e. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Using different RBSs so that secondary structures and self pairing don't occur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Elliott Lui and Jesse Palmer

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence provided here is from the CL1136 strain, with an Arg67Cys mutation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for the glucose-1-phosphate adenylyltransferase enzyme, utilized in the rate-limiting first step of e coli glycogen biosynthesis (as described in EcoCyc database). See http://BioCyc.org/ECOLI/NEW-IMAGE?type=GENE&object=EG10379 for full enzyme details.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This mutation results in greater glycogen production compared to WT.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jesse Palmer, Elliot Lui

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (medium), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Vivek Mutalik et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from standard genomic sequence (glgA) for the e coli glycogen synthase enzyme.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for the glycogen synthase enzyme, utilized in the second step of e coli glycogen biosynthesis (as described in EcoCyc database). See http://biocyc.org/ECOLI/new-image?type=GENE&object=EG10377 for full enzyme details.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jesse Palmer, Elliot Lui

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence glgS as provided on EcoCyc database.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for a protein involved in the biosynthesis of glycogen. Overproduction stimulates glycogen synthesis. Influences the first two enzymes in the e coli glycogen biosynthesis pathway (glucose-1-phosphate adenylyltransferase, glycogen synthase). See http://BioCyc.org/ECOLI/NEW-IMAGE?type=GENE-IN-REG-SUMMARY&object=EG11381 for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jesse Palmer, Elliot Lui

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Guillaume Cambray et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli RNA pol transcription terminator designed and tested by Guillaume Cambray at BIOFAB Emeryville. Based on the natural E. coli rnpB T1 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
